eNCA's Lirandzu Themba was at the Mamelodi West police station. JOHANNESBURG - The family of 76-year-old Martha Marais is laying charges against Mamelodi Hospital. They were horrified to find her handcuffed to a bench in the casualty ward on Wednesday evening. Marais had been admitted with a stomach ailment. READ: Health dept investigates alleged Mamelodi hospital abuse The Gauteng Health Department says it will provide answers by Sunday. Newly appointed Gauteng Health MEC, Bandile Masuku, visited the hospital.
